<h2>%%ReferenceStyle%%Journal article, one source quoted in another</h2>
<hr>
<br>
Avoid where possible!
<br>
<br>
It is better to refer back to the original source yourself so you can check the accuracy of 
the quoted material. If the original source is unavailable, use <strong>&#8216;as cited in&#8217;</strong>
in your text. The original authors are named in your text, but only the source you actually 
read goes in the reference list. For example, if a study by Jones and Chan was quoted in a work 
that you read by Smith, you would only list Smith in your reference list.
<br>
<br>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author. (Year of publication). Title of article (that you read). 
	<em>Name of Journal, volume</em>(issue), page numbers. 
	DOI (if assigned)
</blockquote>
<br>
For works without a DOI, if the work was accessed from a website (excluding online academic 
research databases, e.g., ProQuest, EBSCO and ScienceDirect) include the URL in the reference. 
Works accessed from an academic database do not require a URL or detail about the database in the 
reference list. In this case, the work would be referenced in the same manner as a print version of 
the work.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author">Smith, A.</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2017</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Title of article (that you read)">High speed compression for music downloads</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Name of Journal">Journal of Internet Engineering</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="volume">10</span></em>(<span class="hover" title="issue">2</span>), 
	<span class="hover" title="page numbers">154&#45;165</span>. 
	<span class="hover fake-aref" title="DOI">https://doi.org/10.12:3456789012</span>
</blockquote>
<br>
URLs and DOIs are displayed as a hyperlink. 
<br>
<br>
If the source displays the DOI number only (e.g., 10.1036/0071393756), convert the DOI into a link by 
adding <span class="fake-aref">https://doi.org/</span> before the number.
<br>
